pulltitle: Make Negatus build and mostly work on Windows with MSVC
pullsbody:
Pretty straightforward, I fiddled the Makefiles a bit to make things easier for myself. We could collapse them back together without too much effort but I didn't feel that motivated.

Visual C++ doesn't like initializing stack arrays with variable size, so I changed all instances of those to std::vector<char>.

I didn't implement a few of the time commands (uptime, settime) and I forgot to implement kill. I don't think ps actually works properly either, since it's parsing the output of ps. A few of the other commands don't work because they're Linux or Android specific, but that's no worse than the current state on OS X either.
pull_repo_desc: C++ version of the Android Java SUTAgent
pull_commit_message: Make Negatus build and mostly work on Windows with MSVC

pulltitle: Quick fix for b2g pandaboards and README update
pullsbody:
This is a quick hack to get execsu working, since some calls expect this to be available, and you already have su privileges in b2g. It'll need to be properly implemented in the future for non-b2g devices.

I'll need to update the README again once https://github.com/mozilla-b2g/b2g-manifest/pull/18 and https://github.com/mozilla-b2g/android-device-panda/pull/2 land.
pull_repo_desc: C++ version of the Android Java SUTAgent
pull_commit_message: quick fix for pandaboard sut usage. Will need to properly implement execsu in the future
